OL,3,CSouth Korean man who ate to obesity to
OL,4,Cavoid draft gets suspended sentence
OL,6,FHe was ruled out of active duty in
OL,7,FJune last year after he weighed in at
OL,8,F102 kilograms with a body mass index
OL,9,Fclassified as obese, six years after
OL,10,Fhe was deemed fit to serve following
OL,11,Fan initial physical exam, according to
OL,12,Fthe November 13 ruling.
OL,14,F"The defendant consumed high-calorie
OL,15,Ffoods, approximately doubled his meal
OL,16,Fportions, refrained from physically
OL,17,Fdemanding jobs such as parcel delivery
OL,18,Fwork, and drank large amounts of water
OL,19,Fright before measurements to
OL,20,Fdeliberately increase his weight," the
OL,21,Fjudge said in the ruling.
